Then, as the ratio of AF to AG, or of AF to AH changes, the ovals of each sub-class change in kind, and the length of AG or AH determines the size of the oval.¹¹⁶⁷¹

If AS is equal to A6. the ovals of the first and third classes become straight lines: while among those of the second class we have all pos- sible hyperbolas, and among those of the fourth all possible ellipses.¹¹⁶⁸¹
